Given an array and window size we have to return the maximum element in all the possible windows.

Algorithm
We need to find the maximum value in every window of size k.
Instead of checking every window manually, we maintain a deque that stores indexes of useful elements.
The deque is maintained in such a way that:
nums[deque[0]] is always the maximum of the current window
Steps
If the array is empty or invalid, return an empty array.
Create a result array of size:
n - k + 1
Because that is the number of windows of size k.
Create a deque to store indexes.
Iterate through the array using index i.
Remove indexes from the front if they are outside the current window.
while(!deque.isEmpty() && deque.peek() < i - k + 1)
This means the index at the front is no longer inside the window.
Remove indexes from the back while their values are smaller than the current value.
while(!deque.isEmpty() && nums[deque.peekLast()] < nums[i])
Why?
Because smaller values behind the current value will never become maximum while the current value is still in the window.
Add the current index to the deque.
deque.offer(i);
Once we have processed at least k elements, store the maximum.
if(i >= k - 1)
The maximum is always at the front of the deque:
result[i - k + 1] = nums[deque.peek()];
Return the result.


Code:

class Solution {
    public int[] maxSlidingWindow(int[] nums, int k) {

        if(nums == null || nums.length == 0 || k < 0)
        {
            return new int[0];
        }

        int n = nums.length;

        int[] result = new int[n - k + 1];

        Deque<Integer> deque = new LinkedList<>();

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++)
        {
            while(!deque.isEmpty() && deque.peek() < i - k + 1)
            {
                deque.poll();
            }

            while(!deque.isEmpty() && nums[deque.peekLast()] < nums[i])
            {
                deque.pollLast();
            }

            deque.offer(i);

            if(i >= k - 1)
            {
                result [i-k+1] = nums[deque.peek()];
            }
        }

        return result;
        
    }
}
